 -- Brett Smith <tanktarta@blueyonder.co.uk>  Sun, 13 Mar 2011 19:01:02 +0100  

gnome15 (0.5.0-1) maverick; urgency=low

  * Feature: Major refactor, start of work required for KDE compatibility 
    (much more to do yet)

  * Feature: DBUS API expanded and altered (now more object oriented, 
    exposes more).

  * Feature: g15-desktop-service now manages the LCD and macros and must
    always be run regardless of whether the indicator, applet or tray icon
    is used. 
             
  * Feature: GNOME specific plugins removed from core into their own 
    package.
  
  * Feature: Panel applet and indicator have been moved to their own package.
  
  * Feature: New "System Tray" alternative to panel applet and indicator
  
  * Bug: Only allow one instance of g15-config to be running at a time.
  
  * Bug: MPRIS plugin shouldn't need to poll for players, just watch 
    DBUS events 
  
  * Feature: Macros can now be created and edited in the configuration UI
  
  * Feature: Macros can now be used to run system commands.
  
  * Bug: Driver now disconnects when switching users. This allows multiple
    gnome15 instances to co-exist.
    
  * Feature: New g19direct driver (does away with g19d but requires more
    permissions on device)
  
  * Bug: Macros contains AltGr playback now work.
  
  * Feature: Macros are now stored in ~/.config/gnome15/macro_profiles as INI
    style files instead of GConf. This makes it easier to back them up or
    move them and is also useful for the ongoing KDE compatibility work.
    This new features adds a new dependency, pyinotify
  
 -- Brett Smith <tanktarta@blueyonder.co.uk>  Thu, 27 Jan 2010 22:51:17 +0000
 
gnome15 (0.4.1-1) maverick; urgency=low

  * Bug: DBUS API was broken. It is now fixed, and with more functions
    implemented. The example script has been updated to reflect this. 

 -- Brett Smith <tanktarta@blueyonder.co.uk>  Mon, 24 Jan 2010 23:58:47 +0000
 
gnome15 (0.4.0-1) maverick; urgency=low

  * Feature: Support latest models supported by g15daemon. Will 
    require a patched g15tools suite.
   
  * Bug: Plugin will now only appear in g15-config if supported
    by the current model.
  
  * Bug: Plugin will now only load in g15-indicator or g15-applet
    if supported by the current model.
  
  * Bug: sysmon plugin: Erroneous memory unit in g19 keyboards.
  
  * Bug: screensaver plugin: erroneous text alignment.
  
  * Bug: applet: display "screens" list with left click.
  
  * Bug: rss plugin: now correctly refreshes at configured interval
  
  * Feature: sysmon plugin: remembers last CPU / NET selected
  
  * Feature: last selected screen will be reselected when Gnome15 restarts
  
  * Feature: DBUS API. Create and draw new screens over DBUS
  
  * Feature: Allow boot-up keyboard color to be set (g19d driver only)
  
  * Feature: g15-macros no longer exists. Functionality has been merged
    with g15-config
  
  * Bug: Problem drawing theme files that require text boxes on locales
    that use "," as a decimal point
  
  * Feature: New G15Daemon plugin. Allows g15daemon scripts to run on a G19.
  
  * Bug: Notify plugin now cleans up the mess of image files it left in /tmp.
   
  * Bug: Notify plugin now correctly replaces messages with the same ID.
    This improves the problem with Rhythmbox hanging when tracks change,
    although does not fix it completely. 

 -- Brett Smith <tanktarta@blueyonder.co.uk>  Mon,  3 Jan 2010 23:38:47 +0000
 
gnome15 (0.3.1-1) maverick; urgency=low

  * Cycle screens options gets set correctly upon starting g15-config
  * LCDBiff plugin actually counts IMAP mails now
  * Fixed crash in LCDBiff when accessing gnome keyring
  * Panel now has some support for G15 and other monochrome displays. 
  * Many theme fixes and adjustments for G15 and other monochrome displays.
    Main change was re-arranging to accomodate the panel, but other stuff
    was fixed along the way.
  * System Monitor plugin can now show specific CPU or Network Interface
    details cycle with Up/Down on the G19, and L3/L4 on others

